10/04/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- EUFOR Commander Major General David Leakey met on Friday (8 April) with the heads of BiH law enforcement agencies to discuss specific assistance EUFOR can provide in fighting organised crime. Officials from the EU Police Mission and the Office of the High Representative also attended the talks. Leakey reiterated that BiH authorities should assume the lead role against crime. 
In other news, EUFOR announced on Saturday that it conducted a routine training exercise in Pale, Republika Srpska, involving about 100 troops. EUFOR says it was unrelated to the fact that Pale was the wartime stronghold of fugitive Radovan Karadzic. (RTRS, NTV Hayat - 08/04/05)
